<td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" align="CENTER">
<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">In a group of three, I agree you need a tank.  I would recommend a Ranger or an SK to give you some spell casting flexibility.  <p>

You need a healer, so I would recommend a Druid or a Shaman to again give you the ability to adjust to the combat environment.  These two can heal and also give you needed damage and utility spells (ie SoW, buffs, dmg shield).   <p>

Finally, I would take a spell caster with a good pet (Necro or Mage) or a Rogue.  This will give you additional melee punch (and your tank doesn't become the target of everything) And, if you take a spell caster, a good way to quickly resolve combat.  <p>

I don't recommend an Enchanter or a Bard in such a small group, but these two are awesome in larger groups.  A cleric would be too specialized, as would a pure Tank.  Wizards are powerful, and they are the "purest" of the casters (pure nukers); but not a good choice where each character must play multiple roles.  Tell me what you think of this.<p>

Troll SK<br>
Ogre Shaman<br>
Dark Elf Necro<p>

(and don't go near sunlight)<hr>Glaum<br>
SK Troll</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
