<tr>
<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">For versatility here's what I'd do.  I'd get a druid, enchanter, and SK.  Druids have the most versatile spells in the game.  They have awsome nukes, dots, sow, snare, root, Teleports!!!.  They are a must in your trio.  And enchanter is another awsome class.  Clarity is great and the croud control aspect will save you 1000's of times.  And I debated about saying Sk, pally or war for the last spot.  Many of the SKs great abilities get covered up by the improved ones of the druid and enchanter until over 50.  The main reason I'd go with the sk over the war or pally is Feign death.  But obviously they all hive their ups and downs.  If your nat a cleric you don't really need the massive HP pool to complete heal but wars take less damage which is really nice.  There are many great threesomes in the game but from what I've seen druid/chanter/tank works the best in the most situations...</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
