<td valign="MIDDLE"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="000000">I would say your best bet would be with the following group:<br>
Druid:  Heals, Buffs, DD, Kiting, and DoTs<br>
Enchanter:  DD, Buffs, Debuffs, Crowd Control<br>
Shadow Knight:  Melee, DD, Pet, DoT<p>

This way, you need not worry too much about pulling too much, or what to do if you need to evacuate.  A druid's Teleport or SoW will help you get away quickly.  An Enchanter's Mez will stop those nasty adds, and the SK can just pound away at the poor, unsuspecting fools who stand in her way. ;)  Good hunting to you.</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr bgcolor="DDDDDD">
